==Tailoring==
Cactus Fruit is used in the spool of the [[2 Willow Lane#Sewing Machine|Sewing Machine]] with [[Cloth]] in the feed to create a dyeable [[Tailoring|80's Shirt]].
*Female version: [[File:Shirt136.png|24px]]
*Male version: [[File:Shirt152.png|24px]]
It is a green dye when used in the spool of the Sewing Machine with a dyeable clothing item in the feed. It can be placed in the green dye pot at Emily's and Haley's house for use in [[dyeing]].

==Quests==
*Cactus Fruit may be randomly requested after the player has completed the [[Bundles#Vault|Vault Bundles]] at the [[Quests#Help Wanted Quests|"Help Wanted" board]] outside [[Pierre's General Store]] for a reward of {{Price|225}} and 150 [[Friendship]] points.
*3 Cactus Fruit may be requested by [[Sandfish]] or [[Scorpion Carp]] in a [[Fish Pond#Quests|Fish Pond quest]] to increase the capacity of the pond from 3 to 5.

==History==
{{History|1.3.27|Added ability to grow from [[Cactus Seeds]].}}
{{History|1.4|Added [[Desert Obelisk]] building requirement.  Added to [[Quests#Help Wanted Quests|Help Wanted quests]]. Can now be used in [[Tailoring]]. Can be requested in a [[Fish Pond#Quests|Fish Pond quest]].}}
{{History|1.5|Iridium quality is now possible for grown Cactus Fruit when using [[Deluxe Fertilizer]].}}

